# JVM flags required for Java 17 compatibility with old Swing LAFs and BeanShell.
# This file is NOT auto-consumed — flags must be added manually to your launch command:
#
#   java <flags-from-here> -Djava.system.class.loader=pl.mpak.startup.StartupClassLoader -jar startup.jar
#
# If you encounter InaccessibleObjectException at runtime, add the required flag here
# and to your launch script/shortcut. Common candidates for old Swing LAFs:
#
#   --add-opens=java.desktop/sun.awt=ALL-UNNAMED
#   --add-opens=java.desktop/com.sun.java.swing.plaf.windows=ALL-UNNAMED
#   --add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED
#   --add-opens=java.base/java.lang.reflect=ALL-UNNAMED
